# FreeCAD Future Boundary Rules

## Keep FreeCAD optional

- FreeCAD integration is planned, but the core solver must remain usable without FreeCAD installed.
- Do not add mandatory FreeCAD imports to core modules.
- Any FreeCAD-specific dependency must be isolated under `thermal_solver/freecad/`.

## Treat FreeCAD as an adapter layer

FreeCAD code should primarily handle:
- extracting geometry or metadata from FreeCAD
- mapping FreeCAD data into `ThermalModel` or related core structures
- launching shared execution through `run_case()` or equivalent shared service APIs
- mapping results back to FreeCAD objects for visualization

## Do not embed solver logic into FreeCAD adapters

- Numerical logic belongs in `thermal_solver/solvers/`.
- Parsing and model construction belong in core package modules.
- FreeCAD adapters should translate data, not own the solver.

## Preserve headless usability

- Core solver code should remain testable and runnable in plain Python.
- Do not make core imports fail just because FreeCAD is unavailable.